parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Electronic Throttle Module (ETM) can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
the ETS (Electronic Throttle System) warning light illuminates
the engine surges or hesitates
the vehicle accelerates or decelerates erratically
the throttle response is slow or unresponsive
and the vehicle vibrates or shakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ETS can cause the vehicle to suddenly lose power, stall, or hesitate, which can lead to accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The ETS light comes on
the vehicle loses power
stalls
or hesitates
and may experience sudden acceleration or deceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power, which can lead to accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ETM can cause the engine to stall, resulting in loss of power, uneven acceleration, and surging while driving, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine idles roughly
